Assign dimension names to the model solution and toxicokinetic (TK) summary arrays

Source: R/ADME_outputfuncs.R
AssignArrayNames.Rd

This function names the rows, columns, and pages of the model solution and TK summary arrays

Usage

AssignArrayNames(sol, modsol, tk_sum_array, pars)

Arguments

sol

The solution array for all compounds; each page of the array is a matrix that's the concentration-time solution from solve_model for a particular compound

modsol

The matrix resulting from solve_model, where rows represent a time step and columns represent a model compartment

tk_sum_array

The array of TK summary data where each page of the array represents the TK summary of a particular compound with rows representing each model compartment and columns being Tmax, Cmax, and AUC

pars

A list of all user input parameters for the entire app

Value

A list of two arrays, the model solution array and the TK summary array

See also

modsol(), which calls the current function
